bait station
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a tube or other device to hold poisoned bait to eradicate pest animals such as possums, rats, etc, without endangering birds and other Good Things.
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: Jim Cameron writes: Not in OED, DNZE, NSOD or Collins. Frequent use in books, articles etc relating to conservation.
